text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described in 1979 by Robert Chinnock and the description was published in Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Garden. The specific epithet (verrucosa) is a Latin word meaning "full of warts".There are two subspecies:

Eremophila verrucosa  Chinnock subsp. verrucosa which has interlacing branched hairs on the outside of the petal tube;
Eremophila verrucosa subsp. brevistellata Chinnock  which has hairs on the outside of the petal tube with short branches which are not interlaced.
